Table \ref{Results} summarizes the results for each HV value and magnetic field direction. We take the average over the two magnetic field directions for both 10 and 6 kV and then take the inverse error squared weighted average of the 10 and 6 kV results to find our EDM frequency shift $\eta_{\mathbf{B}}\cdot\Delta\omega_{EDM} = (-1.34 \pm 1.67) \times 10^{-11}$ (kV$\cdot$s/cm)$^{-1},$ which gives us an EDM of $\mathbf{d}_{Hg} = (-2.20 \pm 2.75_{stat}) \times 10^{-30}$ $e\cdot$cm.

